# QC Toolbox — ASL MRI Quality Control

[![CI](https://github.com/OSIPI/qc-toolbox/actions/workflows/ci.yml/badge.svg)](https://github.com/OSIPI/qc-toolbox/actions)
[![Python 3.9+](https://img.shields.io/badge/python-3.9%2B-blue.svg)](https://www.python.org/)
[![License: Apache 2.0](https://img.shields.io/badge/license-Apache%202.0-green.svg)](https://opensource.org/licenses/Apache-2.0)

A comprehensive quality control toolbox for **Arterial Spin Labeling (ASL) MRI** data, developed as part of **GSoC 2026** under [OSIPI](https://www.osipi.org/) (Open Science Initiative for Perfusion Imaging).

---

## Scientific Background

ASL MRI magnetically labels water in arterial blood to measure **cerebral blood flow (CBF)** non-invasively. CBF maps are prone to multiple artifacts:

| Artifact | Cause |
|---|---|
| Motion corruption | Head movement during acquisition |
| Low SNR | ~1% signal change from labeled blood |
| Incomplete labeling | RF coil inhomogeneity |
| Negative CBF | Subtraction errors or pattern inversion |

The **Quality Exclusion Index (QEI)** from Dolui et al. (JMRI 2024) is the core metric:

```
QEI = ∛( (1 − exp(α · PSS^β)) · exp(−(γ · DI^δ + ε · nGMCBF^ζ)) )
```

With coefficients: α=−3.0126, β=2.4419, γ=0.054, δ=0.9272, ε=2.8478, ζ=0.5196.

---

## Installation

```bash
git clone https://github.com/OSIPI/qc-toolbox.git
cd qc-toolbox
pip install -e ".[dev]"
```

### Requirements

- Python ≥ 3.9
- nibabel, numpy, scipy, scikit-learn, scikit-image, pandas, matplotlib, plotly, streamlit, click, tqdm, dipy, nilearn, seaborn

---

## Quick Start

### CLI Usage

```bash
# Run full QC pipeline
qc-toolbox run --bids /path/to/bids --output /path/to/output

# Use a specific threshold profile
qc-toolbox run --bids /path/to/bids --output ./output --profile pediatric

# Validate BIDS structure
qc-toolbox validate-bids --bids /path/to/bids

# Generate reports from results
qc-toolbox report --results ./output/qc_results.csv --output ./reports --format all

# Learn thresholds from your data
qc-toolbox learn-thresholds --results ./output/qc_results.csv --output ./thresholds.json

# Launch interactive dashboard
qc-toolbox dashboard --results ./output/qc_results.csv
```

### Python API

```python
from qc_toolbox.pipeline import QCPipeline

pipeline = QCPipeline(
    bids_dir="/path/to/bids",
    output_dir="/path/to/output",
    threshold_profile="default",
    n_workers=4,
)
results_df = pipeline.run()
print(results_df[["subject_id", "qei", "overall_flag"]])
```

### Individual Metrics

```python
from qc_toolbox.metrics.qei import QEIMetric
from qc_toolbox.core.tissue_masks import TissueMaskDeriver

# Derive masks
deriver = TissueMaskDeriver()
masks = deriver.derive(cbf_map, affine)

# Compute QEI
qei = QEIMetric()
result = qei.compute(cbf_map, masks.gm_prob, masks.wm_prob, affine)
print(f"QEI: {result.qei_score:.3f} — {'PASS' if result.pass_flag else 'FAIL'}")
```

---

## Metrics

| Metric | Module | Description | Pass Threshold |
|---|---|---|---|
| **QEI** | `metrics.qei` | Quality Exclusion Index (Dolui 2024) | ≥ 0.70 |
| **Motion** | `metrics.motion` | Framewise displacement & DVARS | Mean FD ≤ 0.5 mm |
| **Control-Label** | `metrics.control_label` | Pattern validation & inversion detection | Valid + not inverted |
| **M0** | `metrics.m0_checker` | M0 signal range, saturation, dropout | All checks pass |
| **SNR** | `metrics.snr` | Temporal, spatial, ROI SNR | tSNR ≥ 10 |
| **Histogram** | `metrics.histogram` | CBF distribution analysis | Mean GM CBF ∈ [10, 120] |
| **Tissue Mask QA** | `metrics.tissue_mask_qa` | Coverage, components, symmetry | All checks pass |
| **Spatial CoV** | `metrics.spatial_cov` | Coefficient of variation | ≤ 80% |

---

## Threshold Profiles

| Profile | Population | File |
|---|---|---|
| `default` | Healthy adults | `thresholds/profiles/default.json` |
| `pediatric` | Children (higher CBF) | `thresholds/profiles/pediatric.json` |
| `elderly` | Older adults (lower CBF) | `thresholds/profiles/elderly.json` |

Custom profiles can be learned from your data with `qc-toolbox learn-thresholds`.

---

## Dashboard

Launch the interactive Streamlit dashboard:

```bash
qc-toolbox dashboard --results qc_results.csv --port 8501
```

Pages: **Run QC** · **Subject Viewer** · **Population Overview** · **Threshold Editor** · **Site Comparison** · **Export**

---

## Testing

```bash
pytest tests/ -v --tb=short --cov=qc_toolbox
```

Tests use synthetic NIfTI generators (`tests/synthetic/generators.py`) that produce controlled-quality data for deterministic assertions.

